If the JavaScript entered for Task 3 is changed to this:

myrow=this.getRowData();
CustName = myrow.getExpressionValue("row[CUSTOMERNAME]");
if (CustName.indexOf("Mini") != -1)
countOfMinis +=1; 

or to this:

CustName = this.getRowData().getExpressionValue("row[CUSTOMERNAME]");
if (CustName.indexOf("Mini") != -1)
countOfMinis +=1;

The example executes correctly.  I am guessing that there is a bug when Rhino tries to parse the JavaScript.  It is getting confused on the word "row".  I'm not sure if this is a bug with the way the script is written, or that BIRT is not escaping the keyword "row" correctly in the getExpressionValue() method.

I reproduced this problem on both BIRT 2.1.1 and BIRT 2.2 M1 on Windows XP.

I have reported this problem on the birt newsgroup list too.  If I should enter another bugzilla for the tutorial documentation, please let me know.
